radiographic_examinations.findings: No focal concerning lung lesions noted; severe hepatic steatosis with a vague region suggestive of focal fatty deposition; normal homogeneous enhancement of pancreas with very mild edema and peripancreatic stranding; no significant pancreatic ductal dilatation or vascular complications; no pseudocysts; no significant free fluid in the retroperitoneum; unremarkable remaining intra-abdominal organs; degenerative changes in the spine.
